  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 3:17-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Further development of the truth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 3:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", by means of recapitulation of the other main points of the Scripture citation. It was just this perverse totality of the Israelites with whom God was wroth on account of their sin forty years long, and against whom, on account of their disobedience, He closed by an oath the entrance into His ",
        "children": []
