  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The interrogation still continued. \"With whom was he displeased forty years? Was it not with them?\" etc.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Carcasses (τὰ κῶλα)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "N.T.o. lxx for פֶּֽגֶר, a corpse. Κῶλον properly a limb. The idea of dismemberment underlies the use of the word. Comp. Numbers 14:29 (lxx), and 1 Corinthians 10:5, of the rebellious Israelites, who κατεστρώθησαν ἐν τῇ ἐρήμῳ were strewn down along in the wilderness. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "N.T.o. lxx for פֶּֽגֶר, a corpse. Κῶλον properly a limb. The idea of dismemberment underlies the use of the word. Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 14:29",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (lxx), and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Corinthians 10:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", of the rebellious Israelites, who κατεστρώθησαν ἐν τῇ ἐρήμῳ were strewn down along in the wilderness. ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
